videos.headline: Bulldogs strike first with rushing TD
videos.description: Mississippi State quarterback Nick Fitzgerald keeps the ball and runs it in 3 yards for the touchdown to put the Bulldogs up early.

videos.headline: Fitzgerald scrambles to escape a sack
videos.description: On third down, Nick Fitzgerald is nearly sacked by Mark McLaurin but he gets free and completes a pass to Donald Gray.

videos.headline: Kentucky gets lucky bounce for TD
videos.description: Stephen Johnson breaks for a 19-yard run and fumbles the ball before reaching the end zone, but it is recovered by Blake Bone for a touchdown.

videos.headline: Fitzgerald shows off dual-threat with long TD
videos.description: Nick Fitzgerald uses his legs as he breaks for a 40-yard touchdown to extend the Bulldogs' lead before the half.

videos.headline: Mullen happy with solid first half
videos.description: Mississippi State head coach Dan Mullen says he likes the way Nick Fitzgerald is managing the game but would like to see more intensity on both sides of the ball.

videos.headline: Fitzgerald strikes again with passing TD
videos.description: Nick Fitzgerald fires one to Jordan Thomas in the end zone for a 10-yard score to extend the Bulldogs' lead.

videos.headline: Bulldogs defense creates interception
videos.description: Stephen Johnson's pass is batted down and then intercepted by Braxton Hoyett which gives Mississippi State the ball with a minute left in the third quarter.

videos.headline: Mississippi State scores on 9-yard TD run
videos.description: While Nick Fitzgerald was out for a play, Keytaon Thompson runs the ball 9-yards for a touchdown to add to the Bulldogs' lead.

videos.headline: Bulldogs defense gets big pick-six
videos.description: Stephen Johnson's pass is intercepted by Gerri Green and he returns it 84 yards for a touchdown to blow the game open for Mississippi State.

videos.headline: Thompson rips off 40-yard TD run
videos.description: Keytaon Thompson runs to the left side and uses his speed to get to the end zone to extend Mississippi State's lead in the fourth quarter.

videos.headline: Mullen likes Fitzgerald as a game manager
videos.description: MSU head coach Dan Mullen says he likes the way Nick Fitzgerald managed the game and the way his defense stepped up in the second half in the Bulldogs' win.
